Explanations for the functions

download.file: download the online data. "destfile" specifies the directory for the download.
unzip: unzip the download data. the default path is the working directory
read.table: read the file into R
rbind: combines dataframes
grep: used for searching if there are elements that match the characters we specify. in this context, it is used to search which
      columns are means and standard errors.
join: function for merging
ddply: used to apply certain function to dataframe subsetting by certain column. "colwise" specify to apply the function to all
      columns

